# Normalize line endings so Windows checkouts don't churn the whole tree with
# LF→CRLF diffs (the autocrlf warning seen on the PR0–PR4 commit). Git stores
# text as LF; working-tree EOL follows each dev's core.autocrlf. Existing commits
# are untouched until a file is next edited — we intentionally do NOT renormalize
# the whole repo here (that would be one noisy commit for zero behaviour change).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never touch their bytes (PNG icons are generated, not text).
*.png binary
